data.enText: the money that you make in business or by selling things, especially after paying the costs involved

data.chText: 收益的上升 / 增长 / 跌落 / 下降
data.enText: a rise/an increase/a drop/a fall in profits

data.chText: 公司在这笔生意中获利颇丰。
data.enText: The company made a healthy profit on the deal.
Net profit (= after you have paid costs and tax) was up 16.1%.

data.chText: 这笔生意带来了创纪录的收益。
我们卖掉这座房子应该可以获利。
data.enText: We should be able to sell the house at a profit .

data.chText: 这个机构是义务性的，不是为了赢利。
data.enText: The agency is voluntary and not run for profit .
the advantage that you get from doing sth

data.chText: 未来的律师研读这一文本也许会有裨益。
data.enText: Future lawyers could study this text with profit.

data.chText: 获益；得到好处；对…有用（或有益）
data.enText: to get sth useful from a situation; to be useful to sb or give them an advantage
Farmers are profiting from the new legislation.

data.chText: 我们努力从错误中吸取教训。
data.enText: We tried to profit by our mistakes (= learn from them) .

data.chText: 当地的许多人认为，这项开发将对他们有利。
data.enText: Many local people believe the development will profit them.

simple_means.memory_skill: pro 在前 + fit〔= fict 做，制作〕→ 在别人之前做〔才会有利益〕→ 利润

ex.enText: They gained an advantage over their enemy.

ex.chText: 这家酒店很小，但有个优点就是离汽车站近。
ex.enText: The hotel is small, but it does have the advantage of being close to the bus station.

synonyms.bx: 指有助于获得成功的因素或某事有利的方面。

ex.enText: He stopped smoking for his own benefit.

ex.chText: 清晨早起对这位病人的健康非常有益。
ex.enText: Getting up early in the morning is of great benefit to this patient's health.

synonyms.bx: 最常用词，指任何利益或好处。

ex.chText: 整天看电视没什么好处。
ex.enText: There's no profit in watching TV all day long.

ex.chText: 学生做这些练习也许会有裨益。
ex.enText: Students could do these exercises with profit.

tr: the advantageous quality of being beneficial
the excess of revenues over outlays in a given period of time (including depreciation and other non-cash expenses)

example: The company has not profited from the merger
She profited from his vast experience

value.def: A profit is an amount of money that you gain when you are paid more for something than it cost you to make, get, or do it.

example.ex: The bank made pre-tax profits of £3.5 million...
example.tran: 这家银行的税前利润为350万英镑。

example.ex: You can improve your chances of profit by sensible planning...
example.tran: 你可以通过合理计划来提高盈利的机会。

example.ex: The profit motive is inherently at odds with principles of fairness and equity.
example.tran: 盈利动机天生就与公平和公正的原则相抵触。

value.def: If you profit from something, you earn a profit from it.

example.ex: Footballers are accustomed to profiting handsomely from bonuses...
example.tran: 足球运动员对获取丰厚的奖金已习以为常。

example.ex: He has profited by selling his holdings to other investors...
example.tran: 他将自己的股票卖给其他投资者，从中获利。

example.ex: The dealers profited shamefully at the expense of my family.
example.tran: 这些经销商通过损害我家人的利益不光彩地赚钱。

value.def: If you profit from something, or it profits you, you gain some advantage or benefit from it.

example.ex: Jennifer wasn't yet totally convinced that she'd profit from a more relaxed lifestyle...
example.tran: 珍尼弗还不完全相信更轻松的生活方式会对她有好处。

example.ex: So far the French alliance had profited the rebels little...
example.tran: 到目前为止叛军都没有从法国同盟那里获得什么好处。

example.ex: Whom would it profit to terrify or to kill James Sinclair?
example.tran: 恐吓或者干掉詹姆斯·辛克莱对谁会有好处？

example.ex: The artist found much to his profit in the Louvre.
example.tran: 这位艺术家从卢浮宫受益颇多。

value.tran: 得益（于）；对…有益；对…有好处
